| `lib/supabase-server.ts` | Lazy `getSupabaseAdmin()` |
| `proxy.ts` | Request-based auth routing (Next.js 16, replaces middleware.ts) |
| `supabase/schema.sql` | Full DB schema + RLS policies |
| `CLAUDE.md` | **Single source of truth** for all known bugs and working patterns — read before any implementation |

## Database Tables
```
raw_stories           -- shared scraped pool (no user_id)
user_raw_scored       -- per-user scoring completion tracking
scored_stories        -- per-user scored stories
user_api_credentials  -- encrypted BYOK Anthropic keys
api_usage             -- token tracking per Claude call
user_profiles         -- profile jsonb + scoring_markdown + questionnaire_answers + synthesized_at
push_subscriptions    -- Web Push per user
filter_user_throttle  -- 90s rate limit per user
scrape_user_throttle  -- scrape rate limit per user
```

## Cost Controls
- Haiku only in `lib/filter.ts` — target < $3/month
- Sonnet only for one-shot profile synthesis — one call per onboarding, user BYOK
- Pre-filter by keyword before Claude (halves token usage)
- Strip markdown fences before `JSON.parse` on all Claude responses: `.replace(/^```json\s*/i, '').replace(/^```\s*/i, '').replace(/```\s*$/i, '').trim()`
- Log every Claude call: `api_usage.insert({ user_id, input_tokens, output_tokens, estimated_cost })`

## Delivery Workflow (mandatory)
1. Read `CLAUDE.md` learning log in full before writing any code
2. Implement smallest vertical slice that compiles
3. `npm run lint` + `npm run build` — fix before proceeding
4. Append new bugs or patterns to `CLAUDE.md` learning log
5. Repeat
